# 4. Core Abstractions

## 4.1 Execution Context

Every component receives the same kind of context.

```python
@dataclass
class ExecutionContext:
    source: Source
    source_key: str | None = None
    mapping: "BaseMapping | None" = None
    metadata: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
    params: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
```

This lets every operation, analyzer, visualizer, GIS tool, or view work against the same source-processing contract.

---

## 4.2 Component Result

```python
@dataclass
class ComponentResult:
    component_key: str
    result_type: str
    data: Any = None
    artifacts: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    metadata: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
    lineage: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
```

Examples:

```text
operation result -> derived Source or DataFrame
analysis result -> numerical/statistical dictionary
view result -> serializable display model
visualization result -> artifact path + render metadata
GIS result -> GeoDataFrame/DataFrame/relationship graph
topology result -> graph dictionary
```

---

## 4.3 Validation Result

```python
@dataclass
class ValidationResult:
    ok: bool
    errors: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    warnings: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)
```

Every component should validate before execution.

