# 5. Generalized Mapping System

## 5.1 Base Mapping

A mapping is not a column mapping or row mapping. It is a general rule system that binds names, roles, selectors, metadata, and derived meanings to parts of a source.

```python
class BaseMapping(ABC):
    mapping_key: str
    display_name: str

    @abstractmethod
    def resolve(self, context: ExecutionContext) -> "ResolvedMapping":
        ...
```

---

## 5.2 Mapping Target

```python
@dataclass
class MappingTarget:
    target_key: str
    target_type: str
    selector: dict[str, Any]
    role: str | None = None
    semantic_type: str | None = None
    display_name: str | None = None
    aliases: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)
    metadata: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
```

`target_type` can be:

```text
field
record
dataset
sub_source
geometry
time
measure
dimension
layer
metadata
relationship
```

Examples:

```python
MappingTarget(
    target_key="incident_date",
    target_type="field",
    selector={"name": "FIRE_DATE"},
    role="time",
    semantic_type="datetime",
    display_name="Incident Date"
)
```

```python
MappingTarget(
    target_key="large_fire_records",
    target_type="record",
    selector={
        "where": {
            "field": "acres_burned",
            "op": ">",
            "value": 10
        }
    },
    role="analysis_subset"
)
```

```python
MappingTarget(
    target_key="fire_points",
    target_type="geometry",
    selector={
        "geometry_type": "point",
        "lat": "latitude",
        "lon": "longitude"
    },
    role="spatial_points"
)
```

---

## 5.3 Mapping Rule

```python
class BaseMappingRule(ABC):
    rule_key: str

    @abstractmethod
    def apply(
        self,
        context: ExecutionContext,
        target: MappingTarget
    ) -> MappingTarget:
        ...
```

Concrete mapping rules:

```text
RenameRule
SelectRule
FilterRule
SemanticRoleRule
TypeRoleRule
GeometryRoleRule
DatasetRoleRule
LayerRoleRule
```

---

## 5.4 Resolved Mapping

```python
@dataclass
class ResolvedMapping:
    mapping_key: str
    targets: dict[str, MappingTarget]
    source_key: str | None = None
    metadata: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)

    def by_role(self, role: str) -> list[MappingTarget]:
        ...

    def by_type(self, target_type: str) -> list[MappingTarget]:
        ...

    def get(self, target_key: str) -> MappingTarget:
        ...
```

