# 6. Virtual Operation System

## 6.1 Base Operation

Operations are not separated into row operations or column operations. They are generic transformations on a source, selected data region, mapping target, or derived data representation.

```python
class BaseOperation(ABC):
    operation_key: str
    display_name: str
    output_mode: str = "dataframe"

    @abstractmethod
    def validate(self, context: ExecutionContext) -> ValidationResult:
        ...

    @abstractmethod
    def execute(self, context: ExecutionContext) -> ComponentResult:
        ...
```

---

## 6.2 Atomic Operations

Concrete operations should include:

```text
SelectOperation
RenameOperation
FilterOperation
RemoveOperation
DeriveOperation
ExpressionOperation
AggregateOperation
JoinOperation
SplitOperation
SortOperation
SampleOperation
NormalizeOperation
TypeCastOperation
```

These should be general enough to target fields, records, datasets, or mapped semantic roles.

Example:

```python
operation = RemoveOperation(
    target={
        "target_type": "field",
        "names": ["unneeded_column", "legacy_id"]
    }
)
```

```python
operation = RemoveOperation(
    target={
        "target_type": "record",
        "where": {
            "field": "acres_burned",
            "op": "<=",
            "value": 0
        }
    }
)
```

Same operation class. Different target type.

---

## 6.3 Expression Operation

```python
operation = ExpressionOperation(
    output_target="burn_index",
    expression="acres_burned / population_density",
    target_type="field"
)
```

Rules:

```text
Do not use raw eval.
Use pandas.eval, numexpr, or a safe expression parser.
Validate all referenced symbols exist.
Return a derived source or derived dataframe.
Record lineage.
```

---

## 6.4 Operation Pipeline

```python
pipeline = OperationPipeline(
    pipeline_key="fire_cleanup_pipeline",
    operations=[
        SelectOperation(...),
        RenameOperation(...),
        FilterOperation(...),
        ExpressionOperation(...),
        NormalizeOperation(...)
    ]
)
```

```python
result = source.apply(pipeline)
```

The pipeline itself is also an operation:

```python
class OperationPipeline(BaseOperation):
    operations: list[BaseOperation]

    def execute(self, context: ExecutionContext) -> ComponentResult:
        ...
```

---

# 7. Analyzer System

## 7.1 Base Analyzer

An analyzer is a function-like component that acts on a source and outputs analysis.

It may be:

```text
graphable
not graphable
numeric
categorical
spatial
temporal
statistical
topological
```

```python
class BaseAnalyzer(ABC):
    analyzer_key: str
    display_name: str
    graphable: bool = False
    output_kind: str = "generic"

    @abstractmethod
    def analyze(self, context: ExecutionContext) -> "AnalysisResult":
        ...
```

---

## 7.2 Analysis Result

```python
@dataclass
class AnalysisResult:
    analyzer_key: str
    output_kind: str
    graphable: bool
    data: Any
    numeric_summary: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
    graph_spec: dict[str, Any] | None = None
    metadata: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
    lineage: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)
```

---

## 7.3 Concrete Analyzers

```text
SummaryAnalyzer
TypeSimilarityAnalyzer
CorrelationAnalyzer
DistributionAnalyzer
MissingnessAnalyzer
TemporalSummaryAnalyzer
SpatialSummaryAnalyzer
TopologyAnalyzer
```

Examples:

```python
result = source.analyze(
    SummaryAnalyzer(target={"target_type": "dataset"})
)
```

```python
result = source.analyze(
    CorrelationAnalyzer(
        target={"target_type": "field", "semantic_type": "numeric"}
    )
)
```

```python
result = source.analyze(
    TypeSimilarityAnalyzer(
        target={"target_type": "field"},
        base_types=["spatial", "time", "numeric", "categorical"]
    )
)
```

