# 9. Visualization System

## 9.1 Base Visualizer

A visualizer takes a source or analysis result and produces a graph, chart, map, or artifact.

```python
class BaseVisualizer(ABC):
    visualizer_key: str
    display_name: str
    required_roles: list[str] = []

    @abstractmethod
    def render(self, context: ExecutionContext) -> "VisualizationResult":
        ...
```

---

## 9.2 Role Binding

Instead of visualizers directly asking for columns, they ask for roles.

```python
@dataclass
class RoleBinding:
    role: str
    target_key: str
    required: bool = True
```

Example:

```python
ScatterVisualizer(
    role_bindings=[
        RoleBinding(role="x", target_key="longitude"),
        RoleBinding(role="y", target_key="latitude"),
        RoleBinding(role="size", target_key="acres_burned", required=False),
        RoleBinding(role="color", target_key="fire_cause", required=False),
    ]
)
```

---

## 9.3 Concrete Visualizers

```text
ScatterVisualizer
HeatmapVisualizer
HistogramVisualizer
CorrelationMatrixVisualizer
TimeSeriesVisualizer
LayeredMapVisualizer
TopologyGraphVisualizer
```

Each should live in:

```text
app/visualization/methods/
```

Each visualizer should:

```text
validate required roles
load source data through context
apply optional pre-operations
produce artifact path
return VisualizationResult
```

